description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF supported early recovery interventions at national level and decentralized levels and resource mobilization efforts in the context of the COVID-19 education sector response plan, delivered capacity building interventions for administrators, and facilitated the implementation of the annual school census. UNICEF also engaged in evidence generation, policy development and advocacy (on digital learning, gender, learning assessment, school health and school-based violence, and education financing), and mobilized new partnerships with local governments, civil society and the private sector, including through UNICEF’s role as lead agency for the Development Partners Thematic Working Group on Basic Education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
